## Download the Dataset File
SQL_Murder_Mystery.sql

Open the file on query tool and Run the entire script in PostgreSQL (PgAdmin) or MySQL Workbench.
It will create all tables and insert the full dataset.

# Database Schema
The database contains five main tables used in the investigation.

# TABLES
## Table: employees
Stores employee information.

| Column      | Type    | Description                |
| ----------- | ------- | -------------------------- |
| employee_id | INT     | Unique employee ID         |
| name        | VARCHAR | Full name of the employee  |
| department  | VARCHAR | Department of the employee |
| role        | VARCHAR | Employee role or job title |


## Table: keycard_logs
Tracks employee movements inside the office.

| Column      | Type      | Description        |
| ----------- | --------- | ------------------ |
| log_id      | INT       | Log entry ID       |
| employee_id | INT       | ID of the employee |
| room        | VARCHAR   | Room accessed      |
| entry_time  | TIMESTAMP | Time of entry      |
| exit_time   | TIMESTAMP | Time of exit       |


## Table: calls
Contains phone call records between employees.

| Column       | Type      | Description                 |
| ------------ | --------- | --------------------------- |
| call_id      | INT       | Call ID                     |
| caller_id    | INT       | Caller employee ID          |
| receiver_id  | INT       | Receiver employee ID        |
| call_time    | TIMESTAMP | When the call took place    |
| duration_sec | INT       | Duration of call in seconds |


## Table: alibis
Stores alibi claims made by employees.

| Column           | Type      | Description                      |
| ---------------- | --------- | -------------------------------- |
| alibi_id         | INT       | Alibi record ID                  |
| employee_id      | INT       | Employee who made the claim      |
| claimed_location | VARCHAR   | Claimed location during the time |
| claim_time       | TIMESTAMP | Time of the alibi claim          |


## Table: evidence
Contains physical evidence found at different locations.

| Column      | Type      | Description                   |
| ----------- | --------- | ----------------------------- |
| evidence_id | INT       | Evidence ID                   |
| room        | VARCHAR   | Room where evidence was found |
| description | VARCHAR   | Description of the evidence   |
| found_time  | TIMESTAMP | When the evidence was found   |


# How to Use
1. Download the SQL file.
2. Open it in PgAdmin or MySQL Workbench.
3. Run the entire script to create all tables and insert sample data.
4. Use SQL queries to solve the mystery.

